sure that the VfsResource interacts correctly with the VirtualFile. I'll check that it exists, is readable, matches the content length, and confirm that the URI scheme is \\\"vfs.\\\" I'll clarify if the behavior is consistent across these checks.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing structure**\\n\\nI'm thinking about using `rm` in this context, but I wonder if deletion is even necessary. The goal seems to be maintaining a one-to-one mapping with dynamic report classes and generated test class files. Existing generic tests might not be relevant and could violate that one-to-one structure. Since we're focusing on the active class, I should create `VfsUtilsTest`. It looks like I need to consider package naming too—file it under `org_springframework/spring_core/VfsUtilsTest.java` and check the build user-code-filter as well.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_P1u6Ym5URxOA5riO72AqiAoO|fc_0cdae3cc1c28d319016a259c0158848197bc1dad6cec2de29e", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1330, "output": 1389, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30367, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780849630473, "responseId": "resp_0cdae3cc1c28d319016a259bdf311c819797f456643b190201"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_P1u6Ym5URxOA5riO72AqiAoO|fc_0cdae3cc1c28d319016a259c0158848197bc1dad6cec2de29e", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"rules\": [\n    {\n      \"excludeClasses\": \"**\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"includeClasses\": \"org.springframework.**\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780849665626}]}
